# Xenia Portfolio - Cursor Configuration

## Project Overview
This is a React + Vite portfolio website for Xenia Snapiro. The project uses:
- React 19 with JSX
- Vite as the build tool
- GSAP for animations
- ESLint for code quality
- Responsive images (AVIF/WebP format with multiple sizes: 300, 500, 800)

## Git & Deployment

### Repository
- Remote: https://github.com/Katarask/xenia-portfolio
- Branch: main

### Deployment (GitHub → Vercel)
Vercel is connected to the GitHub repo and deploys automatically on every push.

**To deploy:**
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push origin main
```

Vercel will automatically build and deploy within ~1-2 minutes.

**WICHTIG:**
- NICHT `vercel` CLI direkt verwenden - nur über GitHub pushen
- Nach dem Push: Deployment-Status unter https://vercel.com prüfen
- Production URL: Wird von Vercel automatisch bereitgestellt

### Common Issues
- If push fails with "rejected": Run `git pull origin main --rebase` first
- If build fails on Vercel: Check the build logs in Vercel dashboard

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports
- Use modern ES6+ syntax
- Follow React best practices
- Maintain responsive design principles
- Use semantic HTML

## File Structure
- Components are in `src/components/`
- Styles are co-located with components or in `src/`
- Images are in `public/images/` with responsive variants (300, 500, 800)
- API routes are in `api/`
- Fonts are in `public/fonts/`

## Important Notes
- Images should be optimized AVIF/WebP format
- Maintain mobile-first responsive design
- Keep animations smooth and performant with GSAP
- Follow existing component patterns
- Use the custom cursor component when appropriate
- CSS variables for typography are defined in `src/App.css` (:root)

